<HEADLINE>
TAICHUNG CITY GETS DONATION OF 210 WHEELCHAIRS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taichung,  central  Taiwan,  Jan.  15  (CNA) 01/15/07  21:39:39
(By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
The Taichung city government received 210 wheelchairs  as a gift
Monday from a charitable organization and a private company.
</P>
<P>
Taichung Mayor Jason Hu accepted the donation from Tzulien Care
Association and Shih Tung Metals Co. at a presentation ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ceremony, Hu thanked the donors for demonstrating
their  love and compassion  in helping  people  with physical
disabilities to move around more easily.
</P>
<P>
He said the Taichung city government has been making great
efforts to turn the city into a barrier-free environment for
disabled people, and that the job is now 92 percent complete.
</P>
<P>
The mayor also said most of the donated wheelchairs will be given
to 30 old-age homes and infirmaries, including the Taichung Ren-
ai Senior Citizens Home.
</P>
<P>
Yu Chien-hsiung, deputy general manager of Shih Tung Metals Co.
said at the ceremony  that  Shih Tung has been manufacturing
wheelchairs for more than 20 years, and that prior to the latest
donation to Taichung city, the company had donated 200
wheelchairs to Changhua County.
</P>
